The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 UltraTech net at Rs 127 cr

 OUR BUREAU 

 Oct. 16: Backed by strong sales, UltraTech Cement has posted a net profit of Rs 127 crore for the second quarter ended September 30 against Rs 0.1 crore in the corresponding period last year. 

 Cement volume growth at 11 per cent was on a par with the industry during the quarter, while production rose along with an increase in domestic and export realisation. UltraTech said net sales of Rs 1,005 crore was 57 per cent higher compared with the corresponding quarter last fiscal. 

 UltraTech produced 30.71 lakh tonnes (28.24 lakh tonnes) of clinker and 29.99 lakh tonnes (27.13) of cement. Overall sales volume grew 17 per cent from 31.34 lakh tonnes to 36.81 lakh tonnes in the second quarter. Domestic cement realisation increased by 45 per cent over the depressed price levels in the same period last year, while export prices increased by 14 per cent. 

 Geometric Software profit

 Geometric Software Solutions Companys net profit more than tripled to Rs 8.26 crore for the quarter ended September 30 compared with Rs 1.93 crore for the same period a year ago. Total income registered a 74.52 per cent increase at Rs 50.14 crore for the second quarter this fiscal against Rs 28.73 crore for the corresponding period last year, the city-based IT company informed the stock exchanges.

 The group has posted a net profit after minority interest of Rs 10.08 crore for the quarter compared with Rs 3.38 crore for the same period in 2005. Total income of the group increased to Rs 82.85 crore from Rs 50.85 crore in the same period last fiscal.

 HCL Tech bottomline

 HCL Technologies has posted a net profit of Rs 205.83 crore for the quarter ended September 30 against Rs 89.39 crore in the year-ago period. The companys revenues increased 42.1 per cent year-on-year to Rs 1,379 crore, chairman and CEO Shiv Nadar said here. 

 The growth vindicates HCLs emphasis on large multi-service deals which are starting to pay off, he said. 




